Presenting Problem / Chief Complaint: The patient expresses concern about balancing work and personal projects without feeling overwhelmed.
History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient has been practicing mindfulness exercises, which have helped them feel more centered and less overwhelmed with deadlines. They have also started a personal project about their experiences in LA, finding it cathartic and nostalgic. They plan to incorporate contrasts in their photos and have shared their work with a friend, receiving positive feedback.
Psychosocial History: The patient has been more intentional about reaching out to family and friends, resulting in closer relationships and more meaningful conversations.
Current Functional Status: The patient uses a planner to manage their time but still feels pulled in different directions.
Therapeutic Interventions: The patient plans to set reminders for mindfulness practice and aims to break tasks into smaller, manageable parts.
Next Steps: The patient will dedicate a few hours each week to their personal project while maintaining their work commitments.
